By requesting a consolidation you confirm that all selected sections will have the same relevance to RBC and regulatory theme.  It's important to specify which section the other sections should be combined into. For instance, sections B and C should be combined into section A. There are two reasons for this. First, if you are combining sections into an existing section that has already been validated, then a new validation is not required. The chosen sections (B and C) will automatically adopt the values of the existing section (A). Second, all mappings except for those in Section A will be lost.
